<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<section xml:id="definitions" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Definitions</title>
  <p>
    <me>
      A \ \text{graph} \ G = (V, E) \text{ consists of a set } V \text{ of vertices and a set } E \text{ of edges, where}
    </me>
    <me>
      E \subset \{\{u, v\} | u, v \in V\}
    </me>.
  </p>
  <p>
    The set of edges is a set whose elements are subsets of two vertices. Vertices can also be called nodes. Let the set of Vertices <m>V</m> and the set of edges <m>E</m> be defined as follows:
    <me>
      V = \{a, b, c, d, e\}
    </me>
    <me>
      E = \{\{a, e\}, \{a, b\}, \{a, c\}, \{b, c\}, \{b, d\}, \{c, d\}, \{d, e\}\}
    </me>
  </p>
  <sage>
    <input>
      V = ['a', 'b', 'c', 'd', 'e']

      E = [('a', 'e'), ('a', 'b'), ('a', 'c'), ('b', 'c'), ('b', 'd'), ('c', 'd'), ('d', 'e')]

      G = Graph([V, E])

      G.plot()
    </input>
  </sage>
  <p>
    Include the other ways to define a graph.
